The paper focuses on the development of a pipeline that unifies joint image-text embedding models with multimodal neural language models. This involves the use of techniques from computer vision (such as image embeddings) and natural language processing (such as language models). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as LSTM and neural networks, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also deals with multimodal learning, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
